HEADWORD: Megalesian
<hw>Meg`a*le"sian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Megalesius</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>Mega`lh</grk> the Great, a surname
of Cybele, the Magna Mater.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to, or in honor of,
Cybele; <as>as, the <ex>Megalesian</ex> games at Rome</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

